              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1CANSAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 300 MeV  electron  linac  coupled to a",
                " pulse stretcher ring."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The scattering target was liquid hydrogen.  The target",
                " assembly was   a   closed-loop  recirculation  system",
                " consisting of  a  two-stage  refrigerator,  a  target",
                " flask and reservoir,  and transfer tubes. The 0.25-mm",
                " thick mylar target flask was a cylinder 10.16  cm  in",
                " diameter and about 13 cm long."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "     Two  large-volume  high-resolution  Nai(Tl)",
                " spectrometers."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   Statistical   errors    are    given.    The",
                " systematic errors  are  4.4  %  below  350  MeV,  6 %",
                " between 350 and 380 MeV, and 8 % above."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Compton scattering cross section on the proton has",
                " been measured at laboratory angles 90 degree and  135",
                " degree using  tagged photons in the energy range 70 -",
                " 100 MeV and simultaneously using untagged photons  in",
                " the range  100 - 148 MeV.  With the aid of dispersion",
                " relations, these cross sections were used to  extract",
                " the electric and magnetic polarizabilities, alpha and",
                " beta respectively,  of  the  proton.  It was obtained",
                " that alpha + beta =  15.0  ((2.9),  (1.1),  (0.4))  x",
                " 10**(-4) fermi**(-3),    in    agreement    with    a",
                " model-independent dispersion sum rule,  and  alpha  -",
                " beta   =   10.8   ((1.1),  (1.4),  1.0))  x  10**(-4)",
                " fermi**(-3),  where the errors shown are statistical,",
                " systematic, and model-dependent, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
